        <h1>Introduction</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
          <p>
            A great teacher has passed away. His family name Kong (孔), his personal name Qui (丘) - known by many today in the Latinized form, 'Confucius'.<a href="#c-1" class="citation" title="The only other Chinese philosopher known to Westerners by the Latinized form of the name is his most well-known disciple, Mencius - due to the first European interpreters of Chinese culture."><span id="rfn-1"></span>[1]</a> His teachings were magnificent and memorable, as was his life. The life of the master was not short, and there were countless valuable lessons he imparted. The disciples decide to collect his sayings and wisdom and compile it into a book - calling it 'Selected Speeches', or Analects.
          </p>
          <p>
            This text they were writing into strips of bamboo eventually surivive many generations and edits, to be compiled into 20 Chapters. The many outstanding interpretations and commentaries of the text by notable scholars throughout the rich Chinese history become as valuable as the original text itself. Today, the Analects is considered by many to be the authorative text of East Asian Philosophy, paralleling the Bible of the West in terms of social influence.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-6">
          <img height="30%" width="60%" src="images/confuciusdisciples.jpg">
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
